cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it presents a real-time object detector. It also involves machine learning techniques such as decoupling detection and classification, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of position-sensitive filters for localization and the generalization of objectness to novel classes suggest that it could belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the mention of mAP and the performance increase with the number of training object classes suggest that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
